comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-17T23:53:18.340Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation evidence (2026-07-18): tools/call now warns on every nested options key absent from the invoked action's contract, using the exact pm-qxwu mechanism (stderr + additive structuredContent.warnings, never rejecting). Contract tables stay the single source of truth via the new exported pmToolActionParameterKeys(action) accessor in sdk/cli-contracts/tool-schema.ts — the same composition the strict action-scoped schema builder uses (action + global transport params + mutation projection keys + required/optional). Narrow tools resolve their fixed action from the new NARROW_TOOL_ACTIONS map (HANDLERS now derived from it, no duplication); pm_run resolves options validation from its action argument; extension/package actions have no contract entry and keep arbitrary passthrough. Regression spec covers the exact original repro class (pm_deps options.dep mutation-shaped key on a read tool), near-miss suggestions (options.formt -> format), pm_run action resolution, and all skip paths. Live MCP-session proof: pm_deps options.dep warning surfaced verbatim in structuredContent.warnings."
  "2026-07-18T00:37:00.161Z",codex-root,"Review finding: contract-only nested option validation conflates canonical action-schema keys with runtime-compatible nested wrapper grammar. Full coverage remained 100/100/100/100, but integration traces proved valid list/update/checkpoint/project options were incorrectly labeled as no-ops. Fixing on the existing canonical item before merge; no duplicate item created."
  "2026-07-18T00:44:06.703Z",codex-root,"Completion evidence: review found and fixed false-positive warnings for update-many/close-many wrapper grammar and extension/package project selectors. Added an exported composed nested-option contract used by MCP validation while preserving canonical action schemas. Verification: pnpm build; 24 targeted unit/integration tests; pnpm quality:static (including 100% docstrings and package boundaries); full coverage 305 files/5,863 tests with statements 38,560/38,560, branches 27,105/27,105, functions 7,837/7,837, lines 37,556/37,556; git diff --check clean."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-17T21:31:25.688Z",maintainer-agent,"Origin context preserved: discovered during PR #580 when a test assumed pm_deps options.dep mutates. The pm-qxwu top-level warning mechanism (TOOL_DECLARED_KEYS at tools/call) is the intended pattern to extend one level into options objects using the per-action optional lists in tool-schema.ts as the contract source."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T00:44:07.284Z",codex-root,"Nested MCP option validity has two sources of runtime truth: canonical action parameters and action-scoped wrapper compatibility grammar. Warning logic must compose both explicitly; using strict action schemas alone creates false no-op warnings for values consumed before command dispatch."
